  "title": "Scalars and vectors - magnitude of sum",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Vectors <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"vector M\"><math alttext=\"vector M\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mover><mi>M</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"vector N\"><math alttext=\"vector N\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mover><mi>N</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></math></span></span> are parallel to the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"y\"><math alttext=\"y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>y</mi></math></span></span>-axis. Let <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"a equals, the absolute value of vector M plus vector N, end absolute value\"><math alttext=\"a equals, the absolute value of vector M plus vector N, end absolute value\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>|</mo><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>M</mi><mo>→</mo></mover><mo>+</mo><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>N</mi><mo>→</mo></mover><mo>|</mo></mstyle></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"b equals the absolute value of vector M, end absolute value, plus the absolute value of vector N, end absolute value\"><math alttext=\"b equals the absolute value of vector M, end absolute value, plus the absolute value of vector N, end absolute value\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>|</mo><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>M</mi><mo>→</mo></mover><mo>|</mo><mo>+</mo><mo>|</mo><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>N</mi><mo>→</mo></mover><mo>|</mo></mstyle></math></span></span>. A student claims that is possible that <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"a is less than b\"><math alttext=\"a is less than b\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>a</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>b</mi></math></span></span>. Which of the following indicates whether the claim is correct and provides a valid justification?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i2",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The claim is correct, because the magnitude of the sum of two vectors is always less than the sum of the magnitudes of the vectors.</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The claim is correct, because the vectors <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"vector M\"><math alttext=\"vector M\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>M</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></mstyle></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"vector N\"><math alttext=\"vector N\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>N</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></mstyle></math></span></span> could be in opposite directions.</p>",
        "value": "i2"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The claim is incorrect, because the values of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"a\"><math alttext=\"a\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>a</mi></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"b\"><math alttext=\"b\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>b</mi></math></span></span> must be equal since the vectors <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"vector M\"><math alttext=\"vector M\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>M</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></mstyle></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"vector N\"><math alttext=\"vector N\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>N</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></mstyle></math></span></span> are parallel.</p>",
        "value": "i3"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The claim is incorrect, because the values of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"a\"><math alttext=\"a\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>a</mi></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"b\"><math alttext=\"b\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>b</mi></math></span></span> must be equal since the magnitude of a vector sum must equal the sum of the individual vector magnitudes.</p>",
        "value": "i4"
      }
